# Redaction eval corpus v1 — synthetic, leak-safe (NEVER paste a real key).
# Format-secrets are stored split across the "assemble" array so no contiguous
# secret-shaped string ever lands in the repo (keeps GitHub secret-scanning /
# push-protection quiet); the loader concatenates the fragments at load time
# into the in-memory text. "template" substitutes the assembled value for {S};
# "secret_type" marks it as a planted secret (else it is a benign decoy).
# Two cases (context = false-positive-*) are deliberate over-redaction exposers
# that quantify known gaps. Lines starting with '#' are ignored.
